Turkish Equity Movers: Anel Elektrik, Koc Holding Shares Move

-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 
2011-03-17T16:10:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-17/turkish-equity-movers-anel-elektrik-koc-holding-kordsa-move.html
  Turkey ’s benchmark  ISE National 100
Index (XU100)  rose 201.79, or 0.3 percent, to 63,482.218 at the 5:30
p.m. close of trade in Istanbul.  The following stocks were active. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Anel Elektrik Proje Taahut & Ticaret AS (ANELE TI), a
contractor of electromechanical services, rose after announcing
a $41.5 million contract from Sky Oryx JV for the new Doha
Airport. The shares gained 6 kurus, or 2.8 percent, to 2.20
liras, the biggest gain in two weeks. The contract was announced
to the exchange after markets closed yesterday.    Koc Holding AS (KCHOL)  , Turkey’s biggest group of
companies, increased 4 kurus, or 0.6 percent, to 7.02 liras. The
company plans to distribute 550 million liras ($346 million) of
dividends from 2010 profit on April 14, it said in a statement
to the exchange yesterday after markets closed yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Harvey in Ankara 
